      },
      "date": "2012-10-19 01:43:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "75fd9ac065a94b1742841844423da739c77f60a7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-19 02:31:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThere is no requirement for the MGS to have an index, so the index check needs to exclude IS_MGS() devices.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2bd225c29bf129b522159af6222601efee260ef4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-19 11:43:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nActually the LDD_F_NEED_INDEX flag is removed from mop.mo_ldd.ldd_flags in the MGS stand alone case.\n\n/* Stand alone MGS doesn't need a index */\nif (!IS_MDT(ldd) && IS_MGS(ldd))\n    mop.mo_ldd.ldd_flags &= ~LDD_F_NEED_INDEX;\n\nSo we don't have to worry about the index check for the MGS case.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b09f102f423a0b9da6ca47423f1e6a1a49f64f85",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-19 21:30:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nYou're right, sorry for confusion.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fbc3b34b628d12facc9771b8ab7ac72213c4bafb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-19 21:34:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJames, it would be great if you could also add a conf-sanity.sh test that verifies that this is working (possibly in a follow-on patch).\n\nIt would mkfs and mount a stand-alone MGS and a stand-alone MDT filesystem, but don't supply the \"--index\" option should pass, while formatting an OST filesystem without \"--index\" should fail.  Possibly also verify that trying to format a second MDT filesystem without an index (which defaults to 0) and join it to the same filesystem should be refused.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ae1c15bef34d388ad34c37ccaab9dcec0a823383",
      "author": {
