        "author": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@gmail.com",
          "date": "2012-10-18 12:26:16.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@gmail.com",
          "date": "2012-10-18 12:26:16.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-1526 utils: Supply default MDT index",
        "message": "LU-1526 utils: Supply default MDT index\n\nTo prepare for DNE indexing has become a requirement\nfor MDTs and with the latest lustre you can't mount\na MDT that was not formated with a index. While mount\nhas this requirement mkfs.lustre has a bug that allows\nyou to format a MDS without a index and not even warn\nthe user. At the same time mkfs.lustre has to handle\nthe case were a user will not supply a index since it\nwas not required in earlier lustre releases. This patch\naddress this problem by supplying a default index of\nzero for the MDT if no index is supplied to mkfs.lustre\nand warns the user they must supply a index in the\nfuture.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: I45932321885856d97b10630a0667e8338822b199\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
